VSC Shortcuts keys:
1.Ctrl+C: Copy selected text or the current line if no text is selected.
2.Ctrl+V: Paste copied content.
3.Ctrl+X: Cut selected text or the current line if no text is selected.
4.Ctrl+A: Select all content in the file.
5.Ctrl+Z: Undo the last action.
6.Ctrl+Shift+Z: or Ctrl+Y (Windows): Redo an action.
7.Ctrl+Shift+P: or F1: Show Command Palette (access to all commands).
8.Ctrl+P: Quick Open, Go to File.
9.Ctrl+,: Open User Settings.
10.Ctrl+K Ctrl+S: Open Keyboard Shortcuts editor.
11.Ctrl+/ (Windows): or Cmd+/ (Mac): Comment out the current line or selected lines.
12.Ctrl+Shift+M: Show Errors and Warnings.
13.F8: or Shift+F8: Navigate through errors/warnings.
14.Ctrl+G: Go to a specific line number.
15.Ctrl+\\: Split editor.
